# Final Installment: Synthesis ‚Äî the Part 40 deliverables

## 1. Executive diagnosis

The engine's architecture is sound ‚Äî the intended pipeline (typed YAML ‚Üí validated config ‚Üí 2D atlas fields ‚Üí signed density ‚Üí surface nets ‚Üí triplanar materials ‚Üí streamed chunks) exists, is largely implemented in the right order, and is unusually well-tested at the config layer. The terrain does not match the intended model because of roughly a dozen **structural defects concentrated at layer boundaries**, not because of parameter tuning. The dominant failures, in causal order:

The base noise primitive is broken (**Bug 7**): `ValueNoise::hash` produces a constant-stride sawtooth along the y and z lattice axes, contaminating every terrain, climate, and detail field with periodic banding. The non-atlas macro shape is a **tilted plane, not an island profile** (Bug 20: `coastal_inland_factor` is a diagonal linear ramp with a sign error), with a dead-flat seabed (Bug 21) and a mislocated ridge (Bug 12). On atlas worlds, hydrology is inert ‚Äî **flow accumulation never accumulates** (Bug 32: one `.rev()`), so rivers, erosion, wetness, and sediment are all vestigial, and what river exists is carved with an **inverted sign** in the density path, producing levees instead of channels (Bug 33, enshrined by its own test). The coast-distance field is water-side-only and horizon-limited (Bugs 25/26), so **no cliffs ever classify, beaches flood the interior**, and an underwater step-ring encircles the island. Meshing emits every chunk-boundary quad **twice** (Bug 8), putting a shimmering 16 m grid over everything and doubling boundary collider triangles. And the material vertex format interpolates ranked float layer indices (Bug 41), striping every material transition.

None of these require re-architecture. Every one has a localized repair, most under 20 lines. The codebase's own diagnostics doc predicted the majority of them by category; what was missing was the synthetic-terrain test suite that would have caught them (uniform slope, bowl, plane-without-orientation-pass, two-chunk seam).

