## 13. Test plan

The recurring lesson: every High bug had a cheap test that was never written, and two bugs (33, 34's cousin in `edit_boundary.rs`) had tests asserting the *wrong* behavior. The suite to add, all specified per-bug: **unit** ‚Äî noise stride/serial-correlation bounds; sampler edge-clamp; winding with orientation pass disabled; D8 direction on an x-slope; accumulation on a uniform slope; Œµ-flood bowl drainage; carve-lowers-`surface_height_at`; blend tiebreak. **Integration** ‚Äî two-chunk duplicate-triangle + watertight test; padded-sample/edit face agreement; paint-then-remesh dominant material. **Scenario** ‚Äî the seven synthetic hydrology terrains; radial coast transect monotonicity; four-compass inland-factor symmetry; cave-mouth breach scan. **Determinism** ‚Äî golden stable chunk hashes; 50√ó material-blend identity; harness-vs-runtime param equality. **Config liveness** ‚Äî the pattern the dead-config family demands: for each YAML field, perturb it and assert *some* probe output changes; this single generic test would have caught Bugs 15, 18 (partially), 21, 28, M16, M37 mechanically. **Performance** ‚Äî per-chunk `record_density_ms`/`record_mesh_ms` regression ceilings.

